title: Natural Gas Prices Slip on Weak Inventory Data
text:
Natural gas prices fell Thursday as domestic inventories grew more than expected.
The U.S. Energy Information Administration said gas stockpiles rose 69 billion cubic feet in the week ended Aug. 21, higher than the 61 bcf estimate projected in a consensus estimate of analysts surveyed by The Wall Street Journal.
